Police said the suspect got out of the vehicle with a knife. While he was being arrested police shot him. HEIDELBERG A man drove into a group of people standing by a bakery in the southern German town of Heidelberg on Saturday, injuring three people, one of them seriously, police said in a statement.Police said the suspect got out of the vehicle with a knife. While he was being arrested police shot him, leaving him seriously injured. He is now in a hospital in Heidelberg, the statement said.